        <type>void(*</type>
        <definition>void(* MLCameraDeviceStatusCallbacks::on_device_error) (MLCameraError error, void *data)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(MLCameraError error, void *data)</argsstring>
        <name>on_device_error</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback is invoked when the camera encountered errors. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
Invalid: The camera device is not available.</para>
<para><linebreak/>
Disabled: The camera device can&apos;t be opened due to a device policy.</para>
<para><linebreak/>
Device error: The camera device encountered a fatal error such as the Headset device has lost connection or the hardware comm bus is busy and not be able to response and caused a timeout.</para>
<para><linebreak/>
Service error: The camera service has encountered a fatal error and could not provide service.</para>
<para><linebreak/>
Capture failed: The capture request has failed. on_capture_failed or on_capture_buffer_lost callbacks will be invoked when this error happens.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">error</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Represents the error type when happened. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Custom data to be returned when callback is triggered. This data passed in <ref refid="group___camera_1ga6bb597e0ba9f5ef7644aaad5102a30de" kindref="member">MLCameraSetDeviceStatusCallbacks</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
